You used to think you were behind, confused, and just stupid, 
but you were never mindless or stupid. You were learning in ways 
you didn’t even recognize yet. Every awkward mistake and late night 
of doubt was quietly building the foundation you stand on now.

You’re a college student and a working game developer, something 
you once would’ve thought was out of reach. The discipline, creativity, 
and resilience you’ve built didn’t appear overnight. They came from 
choosing to grow instead of staying comfortable.

Be proud of how far you’ve come. The version of you back then was 
trying their best with what they knew. And the version of you now 
is proof that growth is real, earned, and powerful.

Keep going and try harder, everything you do will soon pay off. 
Ignore those people who pressures you. Never let them tell you
what you should do and what you should not do, be your own boss 
in your own effective way.